tion budget across MoRE experts based on their historical contribution to performance gains, promoting specialization and efficiency. To ensure scalability, all components operate in an automated fashion post-initial rationale annotation. CORE is evaluated in low-resource settings across domains requiring deep reasoning (e.g., medical diagnosis with uncertain evidence, legal precedent matching, scientific claim validation), where spurious correlations and distribution shifts are prevalent. We hypothesize that CORE will outperform static augmentation methods by producing not just more coherent, but *strategically informative* training signals, leading to superior OOD generalization, reduced variance, and improved interpretability through expert attribution.",
